cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper proposes a novel crowd counting model using convolutional neural networks, which is a popular technique in computer vision (cs.CV). The model also leverages variation of crowd density within an image to improve accuracy, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of a switch classifier, which is a form of decision-making and classification, falling under machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG). The experiments involve analyzing and processing large datasets, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the model in real-world scenarios, which involves robotics and automation (cs.RO).
